						<summary>

						<p>On a fragment slab lying under a tamarind tree in survey No. 233, near the Gālimaḍāyi tank.</p>						

						<p>KULŌTTUṄGA RĀJĒNDRA CHŌḌA (I).</p>						

						<p>1108 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1030, Uttarāyaṇa Sankrānti corresponding to 1108 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and Incomplete. Refers to the gift of land measuring two <hi rend="italic">khas</hi> for maintaining the perpetual lamp to the god Tripurāntakadēva by Pōtināyaka and Pallavanāyaka, the sons of Gāḍidipāṟti Gadya Prōlayanāyaka. Prōlayanāyaka is described as the soldier <hi rend="italic">(baṁṭu)</hi> of Kulōttuṅga Rājēndra Chōḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
